# Local file (not symlinked to .release/.markdownlintignore) — lex has
# repo-specific patterns below that can't live in the canonical upstream.
# Keep the canonical block in sync with .release/.markdownlintignore on
# every release-sync; add lex-specific patterns under "Lex-specific".

# --- Canonical (mirrors .release/.markdownlintignore) ---

# CHANGELOG is generated by `bin/changelog render`; fragments are
# bullet snippets (no top-level heading, sometimes `<slug>`
# placeholders) — both trip MD041/MD033 for no real benefit. Per
# arthur-debert/release#234.
CHANGELOG.md
CHANGELOG/

# .claude/skills/** and docs/skills/** are agent-authored skill
# documentation. AI-generated markdown often has stylistic quirks
# (in-table section headers, mixed list styles) that are intentional
# for AI consumption but trip strict markdownlint rules. Keep them
# out of the gate; consumers can lint them on demand if they want to.
.claude/skills/
docs/skills/

